                h3.pointHeader II. Use and Processing of Information
                subtitle | In addition to the purposes and uses described above, Massie uses information in the following ways:
                ul.pointPara
                    li To identify when you visit her website.
                    li To provide services.
                    li To improve her services.
                    li To conduct analytics.
                    li To respond to inquiries related to support, employment, opportunities, or other requests.
                    li To send promotional materials, including information relating to her services.
                    li For internal administrative purposes, as well as to manage her relationships.
                p.pointPara Although the sections above describe Massie's primary purpose in collecting your information, in many situations she has more than one purpose. As a result, her collection and processing of your information is based in different contexts upon your consent, her need to perform an agreement with you, her obligations under law, and/or her legitimate interest in conducting her affairs.

            .point 
                h3.pointHeader III. Sharing of Information
                subtitle In addition to the specific situations discussed elsewhere in this policy, Massie discloses information in the following situations:
                ol.pointPara
                    li
                        strong 
                            | Other Disclosures with Your Consent. 
                        | Massie may ask if you would like her to share your information with other unaffiliated third parties who are not described elsewhere in this policy.
                    li
                        strong 
                            | Other Disclosures without Your Consent. 
                        | Massie may disclose information in response to subpoenas, warrants, or court orders, or in connection with any legal process, or to comply with relevant laws. She may also share your information in order to establish or exercise her rights, to defend against a legal claim, to investigate, prevent, or take action regarding possible illegal activities, suspected fraud, safety of person or property, or a violation of her policies, or to comply with your requests or for the provision of services by a third party intermediary.
                    li
                        strong 
                            | Service Providers. 
                        | Massie may share your information with service providers. Among other things service providers may help her to administer her website, conduct surveys, provide technical support, process payments, and assist in the fulfillment of orders.
            .point
                h3.pointHeader IV. Your Choices
                subtitle You can make the following choices regarding your personal information:
                ol.pointPara 
                    li
                        strong
                            | Access To Your Personal Information. 
                        | You may request access to your personal information by contacting us at the address described below. If required by law, upon request, Massie will grant you reasonable access to the personal information that she has about you.
                    li
                        strong
                            | Deletion of Your Personal Information. 
                        | Typically Massie retains your personal information for the period necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. You may, however, request information about how long Massie keeps a specific type of information, or request that she delete your personal information by contacting us at the address described below. If required by law Massie will grant a request to delete information, but you should note that in many situations she must keep your personal information to comply with her legal obligations, resolve disputes, enforce her agreements, or for another purpose.
                    li
                        strong
                            | Objection to Certain Processing.  
                        | You may object to Massie’s use of your personal information by contacting her at the address described below. 
                    li
                        strong
                            | Online Tracking. 
                        | Massie’s website does not currently recognize automated browser signals regarding tracking mechanisms, which may include “Do Not Track” instructions.
                    li
                        strong
                            | Informational Emails. 
                        | You may choose to provide Massie with your email address for the purpose of allowing her to send free newsletters, surveys, and other materials to you. You can stop receiving these informational emails by following the unsubscribe instructions in e-mails that you receive. If you decide not to receive informational emails, she may still send you service related communications. 
                    li
                        strong
                            | Revocation Of Consent. 
                        | If you revoke your consent for the processing of personal information then Massie may no longer be able to provide you services. In some cases, Massie may limit or deny your request to revoke consent if the law permits or requires her to do so, or if she is unable to adequately verify your identity. You may revoke consent to processing (where such processing is based upon consent) by contacting us at the address described below.
            .point 
                h3.pointHeader V. How Personal Information is Protected.
                p.pointPara 
                    | No method of transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is fully secure. While Massie uses reasonable efforts to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure, she cannot guarantee the security of your personal information. In the event that she is required by law to inform you of a breach to your personal information she may notify you electronically, in writing, or by telephone, if permitted to do so by law.
            .point 
                h3.pointHeader VI. Miscellaneous
                subtitle The following additional information relates to Massie's privacy practices:
                ul.pointPara
